The course gives a general introduction to the ethnographic fieldwork methods. It focuses on the main principles of the methodology, how the fieldwork methods and  theories were developed,  how to prepare and carry out the fieldwork, as well as on the ethics of fieldwork.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of research methods, their history and relations with theory, analysis and research ethics in ethnology/cultural anthropology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students will learn about the basic fieldwork methods and the main developments in the theory of the methodology. The students will acquire the theoretical basis for preparing and executing ethnographic fieldwork.
